body:
@bolkedebruin @plypaul this looks very nice to me. 

I do see some potential for collision with master. For example, there is now a State.SCHEDULED that I think would need to be accounted for -- right now it looks to me like only QUEUED and UP_FOR_RETRY tasks ever get sent to the executor, and the reframing of QUEUED semantics encompasses some of the reasons for which the SCHEDULED state was introduced. @bolkedebruin I think you'll need to weigh in on the degree to which things like that need to be accounted for.

Here's a thought. I think we all agree that serializing DAGs (as pickles) and then unserializing them when needed is a Good Thing. However, Dags are often unpickleable -- I think because of jinja templates, iirc. Does the use of SimpleDag get around this? Can we pass around SimpleDag objects via the db and avoid having to always parse the entire dag file? That would be cool...
